{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ja6MAmcqkw1V2CRxLtyQWk","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I now have all the information needed. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n## Summary: max_attempts in Workflow DSL\n\nI've found all files related to parsing `max_attempts` in the workflow DSL. Here's what I discovered:\n\n### 1. **Domain Type Definitions**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow.go` (lines 289-301)\n  - `max_attempts` is listed in the `knownStepConfigKeys` map as a recognized step-level config key\n  - Stored as a string in `Step.Config` map\n\n### 2. **DSL Parser Implementation**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser.go` (lines 461-511 for `parseValue()`, lines 363-411 for `parseStepField()`)\n  - Parses `max_attempts` as a numeric value (TokenInt) at line 468-471\n  - Converts to string and stores in `step.Config[key]`\n  - No special validation in parser; treated as a generic config key\n\n### 3. **Test Files for Parsing**\n\n**Parser Tests:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/parser_test.go` (lines 953-971)\n  - `TestParser_NumericMaxAttempts`: Tests parsing numeric `max_attempts = 3` values\n  - Verifies the value is stored as `code.Config[\"max_attempts\"]` = \"3\"\n\n**Mutator Tests:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/dsl/mutator_test.go` (lines 50-67)\n  - `TestMutatorAddStep`: Tests generating DSL with `max_attempts = 2`\n  - Verifies round-trip: generates DSL with `max_attempts` config, parses it back\n\n**Domain Tests:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/domain/workflow_test.go` (lines 230-247)\n  - `TestWorkflow_ValidateConfig_KnownKeys`: Validates `max_attempts` as a known config key\n  - Tests config with `\"max_attempts\": \"3\"` passes validation with no warnings\n\n### 4. **Runtime Implementation**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt.go` (lines 69-79)\n  - Reads `max_attempts` from `step.Config[\"max_attempts\"]` in the `Execute()` method\n  - Converts to integer with `strconv.Atoi()`\n  - Compares against `readAttemptCount()` to enforce retry limit\n  - Returns \"give-up\" result when max attempts reached (line 76)\n  - Attempt counter management at lines 452-484 (read/increment/reset functions)\n\n**Prompt Test:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/agents/prompt/prompt_test.go` (lines 125-138)\n  - `TestPromptAdapter_MaxAttemptsReached`: Tests retry limiting behavior\n  - Confirms \"give-up\" result when `max_attempts = 2` limit is exceeded\n\n### 5. **Actual Workflow Files Using max_attempts**\n\n**Default Template:**\n- **File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/init.go` (line 23)\n  - Scaffold template includes `max_attempts = 2` in the fix step\n\n**Deployed Workflows:**\n- `/workspace/.cloche/develop.cloche` (line 14): `max_attempts = 2` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/ruby-calculator/develop.cloche` (line 24): `max_attempts = 2` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/mini-redis/develop.cloche` (line 29): `max_attempts = 4` on fix step\n- `/workspace/examples/hello-world/flaky.cloche`: No max_attempts (flaky test demo)\n- Multiple evolution snapshots in `/workspace/.cloche/evolution/snapshots/`: Various max_attempts values including \"2\"\n\n### Key Design Points:\n1. **String storage**: Stored as a string in Config, converted to int at runtime only\n2. **Per-step configuration**: Each step can have its own max_attempts limit\n3. **Attempt tracking**: Uses `.cloche/attempt_count/` directory to persist attempt counts between runs\n4. **Reset on success**: Attempt counter resets on successful completion so limits apply to consecutive failures only\n5. **Result fallback**: Returns \"give-up\" result to workflow when limit exceeded, allowing graceful handling"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3e33ef80a5b90e9c (use SendMessage with to: 'a3e33ef80a5b90e9c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 46405\ntool_uses: 23\nduration_ms: 51753</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id